Quote: "The department has applied for a section 105, and the inmate will remain in custody till the Parole Board has made a decision."... Section 105 of the Criminal Justice Act requires an inmate to serve the full term of their sentence on the grounds they are likely to commit a specified offence within that period if freed into the community.
